description:
&lt;p&gt;The Outpatient Department works in close line with a number of the government targets around patient waiting times and as a member of the team, your duties will involve making patient appointments, using the computerised appointment system and applying knowledge of targets and clinic types, rearranging appointments, dealing with patients, dealing with queries from internal and external contacts, face to face and over the telephone and providing an efficient and effective administration service.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We are looking for candidates who have a Good Basic Education, GCSE or equivalent in Maths and English, and who have clear, concise verbal and written communication skills, to enable liaison with multi-disciplinary teams, patients and carers. You must work well in a team environment, as you will be working within a larger team, and feel comfortable working under pressure.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hours are 37.5, Monday to Friday 8.30 – 17.00&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
